<item>
            <title>[HBASE-6363] HBaseConfiguration can carry a main method that dumps XML output for debug purposes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6363</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Just like the Configuration class carries a main() method in it, that simply loads itself and writes XML out to System.out, HBaseConfiguration can use the same kinda method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That way we can do &quot;hbase org.apache.hadoop.&#8230;.HBaseConfiguration&quot; to get an Xml dump of things HBaseConfiguration has properly loaded. Nifty in checking app classpaths sometimes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
